text: Đông Hải is a rural district (huyện) of Bạc Liêu Province in the Mekong Delta region of Vietnam. As of 2003 the district had a population of 130,557. The district covers an area of 550 km². The district capital lies at Gành Hào. ==References== Category:Districts of Bạc Liêu Province
title: Đông Hải District
